===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}

The upper component {{zh-l|*рҰү¶}} is attested independently in Shang oracle bone script, showing a large {{zh-l|*зӣ®|eye}} with a short hooked stroke. Jiang Yubin (и”ЈзҺүж–Ң) identifies it as the original character for {{zh-l|*зҚЁ|alone}}, while Chen Jian (йҷіеҠҚ) and Guo Yongbing (йғӯж°ёз§ү) read it as {{zh-l|*зҹҡ|to gaze intently}}, taking the non-{{lang|zh|зӣ®}} portion as a figure leaning on a staff. Both words belong to a *dok family associated with focused vision and conspicuousness (cf. {{zh-l|*зҮӯ|to illuminate}}). The form with added {{zh-l|*иҷ«|insect}} first appears in Western Zhou inscriptions for the Shu place name; ''{{w|Shuowen Jiezi}}'' reanalyzes it as a {{w|pictogram}} of a silkworm.

Attested as early as in Western Zhou oracle bone H11:68: {{lang|zh|дјҗиңҖ}} (attack Shu), H11:97: {{lang|zh|е…ӢиңҖ}} (defeat Shu).

